{##
Includes a header according to Bulma's standard.
The header has its text with a Material Design
Icon icon before it.

The classes for each element are predetermined and
may not be altered through this macro.

@example Edit header

{{ form.header(
  'Edit File',
  'content-file') }}

@param  [String]        label         The label text to display.
@param  [String, nil]   icon          The hyphen-separated icon name. The macro already inlcudes the preceding "mdi-". Defaults to "progress-question".
@param  [Integer, nil]  level         The level of the header. Defaults to 2, if greater than 5, parses to 5.
#}
{% macro header(label, icon, level) %}
{% if level is not defined or level < 2 %}
  {% set level = 2 %}
{% endif %}
{% if level > 5 %}
  {% set level = 5 %}
{% endif %}
<h{{ level }} class="title is-{{ level + 1 }}">
  <span class="icon-text">
    <span class="icon">
      <i class="mdi mdi-{{ icon }}"></i>
    </span>
    <span>{{ label }}</span>
</h{{ level }}>
{% endmacro %}

{##
Includes a hidden input field which does not adhere
to Bulma's standards since it isn't shown. It must
have a value set!

@example Product ID

{{ form.hidden_input(
  'id',
  15875) }}

@param  [String]  id      The input's id attribute.
@param  [Mixed]   value   The value the input contains.
#}
{% macro hidden_input(id, value) %}
<input
  type="hidden"
  id="{{ id }}"
  value="{{ value }}">
{% endmacro %}

{##
Includes a single-input field according to Bulma's
Form standard. The form has a static button as a
label, with a Material Design Icon icon before the
label text.

The classes for each element are predetermined and
may not be altered through this macro.

@example Username field

{{ form.single_input(
  'Username',
  'username',
  'account-badge',
  'text') }}

@param  [String]        label         The label text to display.
@param  [String]        id            The input's id attribute.
@param  [String, nil]   icon          The hyphen-separated icon name. The macro already inlcudes the preceding "mdi-". Defaults to "progress-question".
@param  [String, nil]   type          The [type of input](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/input#input_types). Defaults to "text".
@param  [Mixed, nil]    value         The value the input initially contains. Defaults to empty ("").
@param  [String, nil]   placeholder   A text to be used as placeholder. Defaults to empty ("").
@param  [String, nil]   attrs         A space-separated list of [aditional parameters](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/input#attributes) for the input. Defaults to empty ("").
#}
{% macro single_input(label, id, icon, type, value, placeholder, attrs) %}
<div class="field has-addons">
  <div class="control">
    <button class="button is-static" tabindex="-1">
      <span class="icon-text">
        <span class="icon">
          <i class="mdi mdi-{{ icon | default('progress-question') }}"></i>
        </span>
        <span>{{ label }}</span>
      </span>
    </button>
  </div>
  <div class="control is-expanded">
    <input
      class="input"
      id="{{ id }}"
      type="{{ type | default('text') }}"
      placeholder="{{ label }}"
      value="{{ value | default('') }}"
      placeholder="{{ placeholder | default(label) | default('') }}"
      {% if attrs %} {{ attrs }}{% endif %}>
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{##
Includes a double-input field according to Bulma's
Form standard. The form has a static button as a
label, with a Material Design Icon icon before the
label text.

The classes for each element are predetermined and
may not be altered through this macro.

@example Name (First + Last) field

{{ form.double_input(
  'Name',
  'account',
  0,
  [ id, type, value, attrs
    'firstName',
    'text'
  ],
  [
    'lastName',
    'text'
  ]) }}

@param  [String]        label     The label text to display.
@param  [String, nil]   icon      The hyphen-separated icon name. The macro already inlcudes the preceding "mdi-". Defaults to "progress-question".
@param  [Integer]       expanded  Which of the two inputs is to be expanded. Either 0 or 1.
@param  [Array, String] input0    An array containing the first input's data. If a string is giver, it will be user as the input's id attribute, and all other parameters will be set to default.
@param  [Array, String] input1    An array containing the second input's data. If a string is giver, it will be user as the input's id attribute, and all other parameters will be set to default.
  @param  [String]        id            The input's id attribute.
  @param  [String, nil]   type          The [type of input](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/input#input_types). Defaults to "text".
  @param  [Mixed, nil]    value         The value the input initially contains. Defaults to empty ("").
  @param  [String, nil]   placeholder   A text to be used as placeholder. Defaults to empty ("").
  @param  [String, nil]   attrs         A space-separated list of [aditional parameters](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/input#attributes) for the input. Defaults to empty ("").
#}
{% macro double_input(label, icon, expanded, input0, input1) %}
<div class="field has-addons">
  <div class="control">
    <button class="button is-static" tabindex="-1">
      <span class="icon-text">
        <span class="icon">
          <i class="mdi mdi-{{ icon | default('progress-question') }}"></i>
        </span>
        <span>{{ label }}</span>
      </span>
    </button>
  </div>
  <div class="control">
    <input
      class="input{% if expanded == 0 %} is-expanded{% endif %}"
      type="{{ input0[1] | default('text') }}"
      {% if input0 is iterable %}
      {% set input0_id = input0 %}
      {% endif %}
      id="{{ input0[0] | default('') }}"
      value="{{ input0[2] | default('') }}"
      {% if input0[3] is defined %} placeholder="{{ input0[3] }}"{% endif %}
      {% if input0[4] is defined %} {{ input0[4] }}{% endif %}>
  </div>
  <div class="control is-expanded">
    <input
      class="input{% if expanded == 1 %} is-expanded{% endif %}"
      type="{{ input1[1] | default('text') }}"
      {% if input1 is iterable %}
      {% set input1_id = input1 %}
      {% endif %}
      id="{{ input1[0] | default('') }}"
      value="{{ input1[2] | default('') }}"
      {% if input1[3] is defined %} placeholder="{{ input1[3] }}"{% endif %}
      {% if input1[4] is defined %} {{ input1[4] }}{% endif %}>
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{##
Includes a field according to Bulma's Form standard.
The form has a static button as a label, with a
Material Design Icon icon before the label text.
The field is to set and/or show a user's professional
registry.

The classes for each element are predetermined and
may not be altered through this macro.

@example Username registry

{{ form.registry_input(
  registryTypes,
  federationUnits,
  user.registryType,
  user.registryState,
  user.registryNumber,
  'disabled') }}

@param  [Enum Array]          registryTypes     The Enum object with the possible registry types.
@param  [Enum Array]          federationUnits   The Enum object with the possible registry federation units.
@param  [Enum Object, nil]    type              User's registry type Enum object - i.e. one of the given 'cases'.
@param  [Enum Object, nil]    uf                User's registry federation unit Enum object - i.e. one of the given 'cases'.
@param  [Integer, nil]        number            User's registry number.
@param  [String, nil]         attrs             A space-separated list of [aditional parameters](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/input#attributes) for the input. Defaults to empty ("").
#}
{% macro registry_input(registryTypes, federationUnits, type, uf, number, attrs) %}
<div class="field has-addons">
  <div class="control">
    <button class="button is-static" tabindex="-1">
      <span class="icon-text">
        <span class="icon">
          <i class="mdi mdi-stamper"></i>
        </span>
        <span>Registro</span>
      </span>
    </button>
  </div>
  <div class="control">
    <div class="select">
      <select id="registryType"{% if attrs %} {{ attrs }}{% endif %}>
        <option value="" disabled>Tipo</option>
        {% for t in registryTypes %}
        <option
          value="{{ t.value }}"
          {% if t.value == type.value %} selected{% endif %}>
          {{ t.value }}
        </option>
        {% endfor %}
      </select>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="control">
    <div class="select">
      <select id="registryState"{% if attrs %} {{ attrs }}{% endif %}>
        <option value="" disabled>UF</option>
        {% for f in federationUnits %}
        <option
          value="{{ f.value }}"
          {% if f.value == uf.value %} selected{% endif %}>
          {{ f.value }}
        </option>
        {% endfor %}
      </select>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="control is-expanded">
    <input
      class="input"
      type="number"
      id="registryNumber"
      placeholder="Nº de registro"
      value="{{ number | default('') }}"
      {% if attrs %} {{ attrs }}{% endif %}>
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{##
Includes a FORM submit button according to Bulma's
Form standard.
The form has a Material Design Icon icon before the
label text.

The classes for each element are predetermined and
may not be altered through this macro.

@example Minimal Submit

<form id="minimalForm">
  {{ form.submit_input() }}
</form>

@example Submit

<form id="nonStandardSubmit">
  {{ form.submit_input('Salvar Alterações') }}
</form>

@param  [String, nil]   label   The label text to display. Defaults to "Salvar".
@param  [String, nil]   icon    The hyphen-separated icon name. The macro already inlcudes the preceding "mdi-". Defaults to "content-save".
#}
{% macro submit_input(label, icon) %}
<div class="field">
  <div class="control is-expanded">
    <button type="submit" class="button is-success is-fullwidth">
      <span class="icon-text">
        <span class="icon">
          <i class="mdi mdi-{{ icon | default('content-save') }}"></i>
        </span>
        <span>{{ label | default('Salvar') }}</span>
      </span>
    </button>
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}

{##
Includes a single-input password field according
to Bulma's Form standard. The form has a static
button as a label, with a Material Design Icon
icon before the label text.

The classes and types for each element are
predetermined and may not be altered through
this macro.

@example Old Password Field

{{ form.password_input(
  'Senha Antiga',
  'oldPw',
  true,
  'required') }}

@param  [String]        label         The label text to display.
@param  [String]        id            The input's id attribute.
@param  [Boolen, nil]   open          Whether the lock icon is to be open or closed. Defaults to false.
@param  [String, nil]   placeholder   A text to be used as placeholder. Defaults to empty ("").
@param  [String, nil]   attrs         A space-separated list of [aditional parameters](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/input#attributes) for the input. Defaults to empty ("").
#}
{% macro password_input(label, id, open, placeholder, attrs) %}
<div class="field has-addons">
  <div class="control">
    <button class="button is-static" tabindex="-1">
      <span class="icon-text">
        <span class="icon">
          <i class="mdi mdi-lock-{% if open %}open-{% endif %}outline"></i>
        </span>
        <span>{{ label }}</span>
      </span>
    </button>
  </div>
  <div class="control is-expanded">
    <input
      class="input"
      type="password"
      id="{{ id }}"
      {% if placeholder %} placeholder="{{ placeholder }}"{% endif %}
      {% if attrs %} {{ attrs }}{% endif %}>
  </div>
</div>
{% endmacro %}
